pageContext.claim: “People that have died 14 years ago. I registered -- They're registered to vote....You know, when you have hundreds of them voting, nah, it's a lot of corrupt stuff going on but we're getting it, we're getting it.”
pageContext.analysis: Politifact put it clearly, “Dead people on the rolls doesn't automatically mean fraud, and elections officials take steps to make sure that ballots aren’t cast in the name of dead voters.”
